    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-27T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-27T05:00:00-05:00" n="310"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1160: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanoi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-27T17:00:00+07:00"
                            >September 27, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 28—8:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>146. There has been a recrudescence of the seizures of transit cargo by the
                    Japanese military authorities in Tongking. It is confirmed that they have seized
                    among other things 136 GMC truck chassis which were purchased under the
                    Universal Trading Corporation loan and which were stored by the United States
                    Far Eastern Trading Corporation at Phuly about 60 miles south of Hanoi. This
                    morning the Secretary General stated that the Japanese military authorities
                    appear to be making a final clean sweep of all such cargoes—doing so before the
                    arrival of a supposedly responsible Japanese mission which may then disavow the
                    actions of the Japanese military forces in Indochina.</p>
                <p>Sent to Cavite for repetition to the Department, Chungking, Peiping, Hong Kong,
                    Shanghai. Shanghai please repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
